item.title: Engine Certification Data
item.description:
This page provides certification data from various engine manufacturers for past and current model years.

NOTE:

Beginning in Model Year 2011, the data for several industries have migrated to the Verify Database system. Therefore, a difference in formatting may be noticed in the resulting files. Most industries that migrate to Verify will no longer have FileMaker Pro files included.

On this page, there is certification data for:
  • Large engines
    (including nonroad compression-ignition (NRCI) and on-highway heavy-duty diesel and gasoline)
  • Small nonroad spark-ignition (NRSI) engines
  • Marine spark-ignition (SI) engines
  • Marine large compression-ignition (CI) engines
  • Snowmobile SI engines
  • Locomotive CI engines
  • Large NRSI engines
  • Nonroad evaporative components
  • Heavy-duty evaporative components
  • Heavy-duty vehicles

Large Engines Certification Data

Data is provided for Engine Family and Models Information, Certification Test Data in Excel spreadsheet format by Model Year (MY). Early years are a Zip file with FileMaker Pro 7 and Excel files. Later years are in an Excel spreadsheet and include Greenhouse Gas data.

item.title: Annual Certification Test Data for Vehicles and Engines
item.description:
Overview

The Annual Certification Test Results Report (often referred to as Federal Register Test Results Report) includes light-duty vehicle and heavy-duty engine reports for model years 1979 through 1994 and light-duty only data for later model years.  Heavy-duty engine data for 1995 and 1996 is also available. The report contains certification levels (projected emission levels at the end of the useful life miles of a vehicle) and deterioration factors used to compute the certification levels.

The formatted report is not available for 1999 and later model years. The list of Certified Vehicle Models can be used in conjunction with the Certified Vehicle Test Result Report Data file by matching the Engine Family/Test Group and Evaporative Family combinations for a given vehicle model with the test results for that same combination in each file. The vehicle model name appearing in the Certified Vehicle Test Result Report Data does not necessarily represent the actual vehicle that was tested.
